In [32]:

residuals

plt.figure(figsize=(7,7))

plt.title("Normal Q-Q Plot")

Text(0.5, 1.0, 'Normal Q-Q Plot')

To test for normality: Shapiro Wilk Test

Ho: The residuals follow normal distribution

H1: The residuals do not follow normal distribution

In [33]:
from scipy.stats import shapiro
shapiro(residuals)
Out[33]:
ShapiroResult(statistic=0.6040308475494385, pvalue=0.0)

This implies that the residuals are not normally distributed.
